description:
Cozy private room and bathroom just for you. :) Althrough it's in the heart of the city, the room is quiet. You can reach almost everything with a few minutes walk, but the public transport lines are also nearby (5 minutes walk).

Cozy private room and bathroom just for you. :) Althrough it's in the heart of the city, the room is quiet. 

My home is my passion, so I really hope, you will enjoy it during your stay as much as I do :) You will have a renovated, small, bedroom with lofted bed and a private bathroom.

The neighborhood is right in the center:
- metro-buses-trams 5 mins;
- sights/attractions 10-15 mins;
- shops, market, boutiques, restaurants, bars etc. 5-10 mins on foot.

It's easy to get here from the airport by bus and metro, about 50-60 mins, and the metro station is literally right around the corner - 5 mins.

The main trainstations are easy to access by metro:
- Nyugati Railway Station 6 mins;
- Keleti Railway Station 4 mins.

In the street there are plenty of restaurants and bars, but the area is still very safe. In the building and in the apartment there isn't any noise, it is really calm.

Several faculties are located in the area so the residents are mostly students.

The apartment is right next to the main attractions of Budapest on foot or by transport:
- National Museum 10 mins;
- Great Market Hall 5 mins;
- Liberty Square and the Parliament 10 mins;
- Royal Palace of Buda 15 mins;
- Andrássy Avenue and the Heroes' Square, Széchényi Thermal Bath and the Zoo 20 mins.

The apartement is on the second floor.

You can use towels, shampoo, the washing machine and everything else in your room and bathroom. You can also use the kitchen for cooking, and the living and dining space, but it's shared with me and my boyfriend. We have a cat and a small friendly dog, but they are not allowed to go into your room (but you have to close the door, because the cat doesn't care about my rules). 

You can also use the wifi connection, and everything else what you need, and I have.

-------------------------------------------------------

Mon apartement est mon hobby, donc j’espére que vous l’aimerez autant que je l’aime. 

Il se situe dans le centre-ville:
- métro-bus-tram 5 minutes;
- lieux touristiques 10-15 minutes;
- grands magasins, marché, boutiques, restaurants etc. 5-10 minutes á pied.

L'aéroport est facilement accésible par bus et métro, environ 50-60 mins, station du métro est vraiment proche - 5 mins.

Les gares du train sont facilement accésibles aussi par métro sans corréspondance:
- Gare de l'Ouest/Nyugati Pályaudvar 6 mins;
- Gare de l'Est/Keleti Pályaudvar 4 mins.

Le quartier se bouge, c'est-á-dire il y a beaucoup de restaurants et bars dans la rue, mais elle n'est pas dangereux á n'importe quelle heure du jour ou de la nuit. Dans l'apartement il n'y a aucun bruit, complétement calme.

Dans le quartier on peut trouver plusieur grandes facultés, c'est pourqoui les habitants sont notament jeunes étudiants.

Le logement est juste á côté de lieux connus á pied ou par transport en commun:
- Musée National Hongrois 10 mins;
- Le marché couvert de Budapest 5 mins;
- place de la Liberté et le Parlement 10 mins;
- Palais Royal de Buda 15 mins;
- boulevard Andrássy et place des Héros, bain thermal Széchényi, le Zoo 20 mins.

L’apartement est situé au 2éme étage sans ascenceur. Vous serez vous loger dans une chambre privée avec une salle de bain privée. Le lit est sur la mezzazine.

Serviettes, shampooings, machine á laver et tous les équipements de la chambre sont disponibles á votre service. Vous pouvez utiliser la cuisine bien équipée et le salon, mais ils sont partagés avec moi et mon petit-ami. Connexion internet par cable ou wifi est gratuit.
